guide general interpretation of the initial sentence of this section:
   * Apache License 2.0 <http:///www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0.html>
   * MIT License <http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT>
   * 3-clause BSD License <http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause>
   * zlib license <http://www.gzip.org/zlib/zlib_license.html>
   * Zope Public License Version 2.1 <http://www.zope.com/about_us/legal/zpl.html>

  If a license document contains a further restriction but permits
relicensing or Distributing under Copyleft-Next, You may add to a
Covered Work material governed by the terms of that license document,
provided that the further restriction does not survive such
relicensing or Distributing.

   9. Liberty or Death.

  If conditions are imposed on You (whether by court order, agreement
or otherwise) that contradict the conditions of Copyleft-Next, they do
not excuse You from the conditions of Copyleft-Next.  If You cannot
Distribute a Covered Work in a way that would satisfy simultaneously
Your requirements under Copyleft-Next and any pertinent obligations
extrinsic to Copyleft-Next, then as a consequence You may not Distribute
it at all.

