  12. Termination.

  If You fail to comply with Copyleft-Next, then, unless you cure such
failure within thirty days after becoming aware of such noncompliance,
Your rights under Copyleft-Next are automatically terminated. However,
the right to make copies necessarily incident to running Covered Works
shall never be terminated.

  Termination of Your rights does not terminate the rights of those
who have received copies or rights from You subject to Copyleft-Next.

  Termination of Your rights disqualifies You from receiving new
licenses for the same material under section 7.

  13. New Versions of Copyleft-Next.

  The initial License Steward is the Copyleft-Next Group. The License
Steward may publish new versions of Copyleft-Next.  Each version will
be given a distinguishing version number. You may Distribute a Covered
Work under the terms of the version of Copyleft-Next under which the
Received Work is licensed, or under the terms of a newer version
published by the License Steward.

